            {
              "originalPosition": 17,
              "body": "this part was confusing to me. I think we want to establish a couple of facts here\r\n\r\n- we don't want to distribute certificates to all downstream time servers\r\n- that means, in practice, that we cannot have direct TLS connections between client and server\r\n- but NTS KE relies on that direct connection\r\n- that is a problem we need a solution for. We present one.\r\n\r\nso, idk, feel free to use this or rephrase in some different way",
              "createdAt": "2023-12-20T11:09:27Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-12-20T11:20:11Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 23,
              "body": "this sentence is weird. I think the important points are \r\n\r\n- the pool is designed to be stateless in that it does not know to which clients it gave which servers (this is a good thing!)\r\n- the client does not want to use the same time source multiple times\r\n\r\nthat requires a solution, we propose one.",
              "createdAt": "2023-12-20T11:11:23Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-12-20T11:20:11Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 39,
              "body": "the final sentence is confusing, when would this come up? the pool randomly deciding it wants to refresh the connection?",
              "createdAt": "2023-12-20T11:13:01Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-12-20T11:20:11Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 48,
              "body": "I think we should make it explicit that this goes against the NTS spec",
              "createdAt": "2023-12-20T11:13:22Z",
              "updatedAt": "2023-12-20T11:20:11Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 60,
              "body": "I think we should make it explicit that this goes against the NTS spec",
              "createdAt": "2023-12-20T11:13:26Z",
